item.title: [DISTRELEC-7737] CH // Add to cart button missing
item.description:
Hi all

Add to cart button is missing on article with number "774360".
On product family it is possible to add this article to the cart.
item.summary: CH // Add to cart button missing

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Can you please check!

This relates to DISTRELEC-7626, "Products without a valid price can be added to the cart". The Buy button isn't displayed if the item lacks price OR listPrice. This should probably be an AND condition?

Hi Erik

Yes you are right.

Is this FE or BE?

Thx
Will

This relates to DISTRELEC-7626, "Products without a valid price can be added to the cart". The Buy button isn't displayed if the item lacks price OR listPrice. This should probably be an AND condition?

No that not true. If we have no valid price the button is disabled (greyed out) but still visible.
In this case the button is not visible at all.

Um, no. The code clearly deletes the button altogether if there is no price:

			<c:if test="${not empty product.price and not empty product.listPrice}">
				<button class="btn btn-primary btn-cart disabled" data-webtrekk-linkid="${wtTeaserTrackingId}.cart.-" data-product-code="${product.code}" title="<spring:message code='buyingSection.add.to.cart'/>"><i></i>
	        		<span class="ellipsis"><spring:message code="buyingSection.add.to.cart"/></span>
	    		</button>
	    	</c:if>

The <button> section is skipped if one of product.price or product.listPrice is empty. This change was done 2015-09-11 by Nitin.

But then the implementation done by Nitin was wrong.

The button should alway be visible, but disable if we don't want to do the add3cart.

Can you please fix this.

The task DISTRELEC-7626 says "please do not show add to cart button for products without prices.", so Nitin did it correctly. But I'll have it show a disabled button instead if price AND listPrice is missing.

The task DISTRELEC-7626 says "please do not show add to cart button for products without prices."

Yes, it is written like you said but and Niting did it according to the description.
-> But is it nevertheless wrong.
Agreed
Should this go to branch 4.0 (important fixes for production)?
yes
Revised the code to make the button disabled if price is missing. Committed to branches/v4.0. Will, can you test on your local env?

Deployment of v4.0.9 to Q done.

Please test!
Tested OK; products w/o price gets a disabled Buy button (see screenshot)

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Estimation needed(if possible) - This is part of the sprint. Thanks!

Hi,
The redirection is correct. However, when EOL redirection from category to product (as replacement), there is a parameter called "eolCategoryFor" which is not considered on the product detail page.

Hi,
After some investigations, here are my findings:

  1. When trying to access the product 17501763 which is EOL, it checks if the product is still in stock or not.
  2. Since product is not in stock any more, then we try to check the replacement.
  3. The replacement product is not a "buyableReplacementProduct" (see screenshot). Therefore we redirect to the super category of the original product with a request parameter "eolCategoryFor"
  4. In the category, we have only 3 products, 2 are EOL (17501761 and 17501763), so it redirects to the only available product in the category. Please note here that even if we access directly the category URL without any parameter it will redirect to the product 17501762 because it is the only buyable product in it.

/Nabil.
